-- ============================================================================
-- KSCW SCHEMA baseline — placeholder
-- ============================================================================
--
-- This file is the consolidated schema baseline (DDL + triggers + FKs +
-- grants) for fresh installs. It is GENERATED by:
--
--     npm run db:baseline:prod
--
-- which calls `pg_dump --schema-only --no-owner --no-acl` against the prod
-- DB and writes the result here.
--
-- The first generation has not yet been run from this branch. Until then,
-- a fresh install reproduces the live state by running all numbered
-- migrations in order via `npm run db:migrate:dev|prod`. Once the baseline
-- is generated and committed, the fresh-install workflow becomes:
--
--     1. psql ... < SCHEMA.sql                     # all DDL in one shot
--     2. npm run db:setup-perms:<env>              # Directus permissions
--     3. npm run db:migrate:<env>                  # any post-baseline mig
--     4. npm run db:smoke:<env>                    # post-deploy verify
--
-- See PERMISSIONS.md and SECURITY.md for the rationale.
-- See CLAUDE.md → "Migration & Permission Policy" for the rules.
